## PROJECT IDENTITY

OpenDraft helps regular citizens turn raw ideas into structured draft documents — either a bill proposal or a product proposal — through AI-guided Socratic questioning. The AI never generates ideas. It asks questions until the user has articulated their own idea clearly enough to populate a structured output. The document builds live on screen as the conversation progresses. When all 7 slots are filled, the draft publishes to a public feed and is manually routed by the OpenDraft team to the correct policymaker or product team.

**This is not a chatbot. It is a civic drafting tool. It is free to use, privately owned, and self-funded.**

When making any architectural or design decision ask: does this help a regular person make their idea legible to an institution? If not, do not build it.

