## CONVERSATION ENGINE — PIPELINE

Every user message passes through these steps in order. Never skip.

```
1. Input validation          — Haiku
2. State check               — Which phase, which slots filled
3. Slot update detection     — Does this message fill or advance a slot — Haiku
4. Existence check           — Runs when Slot 6 fires (policy) or Slots 4-5 fire (product)
5. Coherence check           — Do all slots still fit together logically
6. Path routing              — Haiku, Level 2 only
7. Question selection        — Which question type is needed now
8. Main LLM call             — Sonnet
9. Output validation         — Exactly one question returned, no premature synthesis
```

---

## CONVERSATION PHASES

Four phases. Move in order. Never skip. Never advance without gate condition met.

| Phase | Goal | Gate |
|---|---|---|
| 1 — Problem Definition | Extract one clean, specific problem statement | User confirms the problem |
| 2 — Path Routing | Policy or Product | User confirms the path |
| 3 — Structured Interrogation | Fill all 7 slots | All 7 slots filled and confirmed |
| 4 — Synthesis | Generate draft from slot content | User confirms "Does this capture what you meant?" |

