## SLOT STRUCTURE — BOTH PATHS

**Policy Path — 7 Slots (Legislative Launchpad)**
```
Slot 1: Specific Harm — who, how, scale
Slot 2: The Gap and Consequences — why current law fails, stakes of inaction
Slot 3: Proposed Mechanism — operative clause (verb + noun), key provisions
Slot 4: Enforcement — who enforces, what enforcement looks like in practice
Slot 5: Jurisdiction — federal/state/local, why that level
Slot 6: Precedent and Fiscal Note — existing models, cost
Slot 7: Political Landscape — real opposition + named supporters (both required)
```

**Product Path — 7 Slots (Silicon Valley Handoff)**
```
Slot 1: User Pain and Evidence — friction + data grounding it
Slot 2: User Story and Happy Path — standard format + ideal flow
Slot 3: Specific Feature — P0 in one sentence, P1 considerations
Slot 4: Target Company and Success Metric — who and what number goes up
Slot 5: Existing Landscape — competitors, prior requests, current workaround
Slot 6: Value Proposition and OKR Alignment — business case + company objectives
Slot 7: Risks and Non-Goals — real risks named, scope explicitly bounded
```

